Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment: I watched this for the first time last night and I strongly recommend it to anyone who enjoys horror, suspense, supernatural, conspiracy theories, or just enjoys a great movie. There are SO few movies these days that are genuinely scary and this was one of the scariest I've seen in a long time. It's not even "horror" in the basic sense, definitely more of a suspense/thriller but very good. I mean to have a good plot and storyline is an achievement in itself these days. I personally think what makes it so scary is the whole "what if" part of your brain being triggered. Everyone has their own opinion of course but to be completely honest I made the mistake of watching it alone at night and I'm a 30 year old man who loves scary movies but this definitely had me a little shook lol Like I said highly recommend it to anyone especially a fall night with a date üòâ

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
Watched this a while ago, but I genuinely enjoyed this movie.  A lot.  Like, a damn lot.  The only sore spot for me?  You guessed it:  the ending.

While the ending would have probably been fine in any kind of action schlock flick, this one was more of a thriller, and that ending seemed so tacked on...  If she got outside, and looked and said "Oh, come on..." and then it cut to credits, oh man...  That would have worked SO well.  What a cliff hanger!

But no, we had to get some action movie cliche crap at the very end.  Ultimately, it's a minor ding on an otherwise fantastic movie that was genuinely tense and reaffirms that John Goodman can play a supremely scary guy who doesn't need to scream and yell, but just be overwhelmingly intimidating with just a look and a calm, yet stern tone of voice that just makes you shiver.

Very claustrophobic, very moody...  Absolutely fantastic.  Just hit stop when she says "Oh come on" and you'll have a winner.

Comment: Hi, I am Russian and I have just watched this movie. I have something to tell, cause I can't be silent I even could not imagine how truly John Goodman was the American character to me in this film. The thing is that I visited the US when I was an exchange student and I happened to live with such a guy like John goodman's character. First he seemed very nice but then in time when I watched how he threatened me and others I found out that he was too cared for what I was doing, every move, had stern and unbeatable principals and I almost had nothing to debate on. He was exactly the way John Goodman played in the movie, I still simply wonder how far, he was very big and fat, looking rough, always smiled but I felt some constant hidden danger in his little kinky eyes, somehow intuitively. Of course, I was not locked in a house like that girl in a movie, but you must understand thst I was in a foreign country and had no other place to go than just stay in his house. When I recollect this memory that makes me feel alike the main character. Later, I found out that that man was in a prison before, because he let a foreign boy stayed with him and the boy claimed to police about his sexual harassment. But he tried to calm down me cause all this was in the past and he still stays under the police check and can't move to any other state. Sure nothing bad happened though he sometimes let himself to curse me pretending on his was joking. In the end of season I returned to my homecountry. The memories of it always comes with different emotions. Sometimes I feel hysterically unpleasant like if I was a little child to care about. I shared all this with you because I wanted to express myself and to know you how unbelievably true John Goodman was in his image, this character now associates me with an American type of men when I think of Americans.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
SPOILER:

Am I the only one who hates these films with aliens and/or an apocalyptic theme? I thought it was an okay storyline. I enjoyed all the tension, suspense and mystery, but i'm really not a fan of these type of endings. I thought there were WAY too many cliches at the end. Once she saw the aliens, I predicted what was going to happen. A really typical ending. And come on, why were the aliens presented as some kind of morons who had just 'inherited' all those capabilities and technological powers a mere 24 hours ago. Really? They couldn't catch a slow ass woman? They were easily tricked? That huge ass alien or whatever it was died from a simple molotov?  

Don't get me wrong, of course movies are going to be different. But the way this movie played out, with the characters and their mysteriousness, the mystery of the story in general, the woman who appeared to have been 'infected' etc, this could have ended very differently. For example, what if Howard had really kidnapped her? That would have worked well with what Michelle found out about 'Megan'. We never even got to even know the truth about who is daughter is, who the woman he kidnapped REALLY is, why he did it etc. I guess that adds more to the mystery and suspense, and ultimately remains unsolvable, which some would prefer. Furthermore, what if Emmett was in on it as well? That he was conspiring with Howard on the kidnappings? OR, what if the woman who appeared to be infected was really Howard's wife and that whole scene was deliberately staged so that Michelle remains scared and convinced that the air is really polluted and therefore decides to remain in the bunker? Wouldn't that have worked better? We never got to know why she appeared to look infected either. Oh well. I guess I would have preferred a classic film with a psycho kidnapped, and some kind of twist at the end (such as Ben paying Howard to kidnap her, and why) where it's not based on anything to do with aliens or apocalypse.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
For those of you saying you hate the ending your missing the entire point of the film. 
This movie is about domestic abuse. From Howard's first moments with Michelle he is more worried about controlling her than comforting her or understanding what's going on in her head. He threatens her with violence when she disobeys he's arbitrary rules. Then seems surprised moments later when he's upset. He terrifies her than blames her for hurting his feelings by not showing him enough gratitude and respect. When she finally escapes she finds new threats waiting, hence the abuse metaphor. That for victims of domestic abuse, getting out of the house doesn't immediately solve their problems. For a moment when Michelle first removes her mask, and learned that Howard was wrong about the poisonous air it seems like the movie and my and honor know of relief in the promise of her problems are over. But they are not. That's the primary reason for the big direct confrontation at the end.

Comment: Don't get the hate for the ending.  It was in keeping with the movie's themes and ideas, particularly in how it's sort of an analysis and metaphor for domestic abuse.  Simply escaping the bunker wasn't enough.  We had to see her actually assert power through defeating the alien threat and face it head on when she leaves to help in Houston to know that she has truly become a stronger person and moved past that fear to become someobe who will confront the issues at hand without just running away.  If it just ended with her escaping, it would have felt like a shallow ending...  with her just being the same person she was right back at the beginning when she was fleeing her boyfriend, inevitably to get sucked back into a cycle of abuse somewhere down the road.

Comment: Perhaps I'm mistaken, maybe my computer took me to another trailer somehow when I thought I was watching a different 10 Cloverfield preview... but I saw a clip showing the inside of a passenger airplane, a Federal Air Marshall (or other law enforcement official in a suit) escorted a man in handcuffs and they both sat down. Next scene, the plane is flying and a large ball of white light is close to the plane, and suddenly, after a flash of bright light, a bizarre-looking creature is on the plane in the aisle.  The Marshall jumps up and starts shooting at the creature which is giving this horrendous screeching noise; end of preview.  I haven't been able to find that clip since, so I can only guess I was misdirected to a preview of a different movie, and not 10 Cloverfield.  Anyone know the movie?  Because I would rather watch THAT flick than watch 10 Cloverfield Lane, although it's now too late and that's almost two hours of my life I can't get back.  I know, just my own opinion and all that, but this sequel that's not a sequel (?) didn't measure up; please understand, I loved the original and most of Abrams movies, in fact. But for the first hour and 25 minutes of this movie, almost the entire movie, our heroine is locked in a cellar with two guys, and there's a lot of emotional buildup, etc., but that's it.  I thought I was watching a Cloverfield movie.  Quite disappointed.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
10 Cloverfield Lane is a tense Horror/Thriller that has you guessing the motives of the characters throughout the film. 
It's the story of a woman who wakes up in a room underground after a car accident and is told by a farmer that he has saved her from the world outside which he says is uninhabitable . The question is , is he lying and does he have an ulterior motive for keeping her captive?
This is a spin off from the 2008 film Cloverfield ( which I loved) but it's hard to say why without giving it away.
John Goodman is fantastic as Howard and Mary Elizabeth Winstead is pretty convincing too. Director Dan Trachtenberg did a really good job with this considering it was his debut feature. 
I really enjoyed this and hopefully we will see more Cloverfield hybrid's in the future.my rating - 8 out of 10

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
*Spoilers*





*-Howard (Goodman) hits Michelle's (Winstead) car in the beginning of the movie by mistake cause her to crash and be knocked unconscious. Howard was rushing to his bunker before the "Attack" and decides to bring Michelle  along with him.

*- Michelle awakens and meets Howard, she is told about the "Contaminated air" and "attack" going on at the surface. She also meets Emmett (Gallagher) who was trying to get into the bunker before the "attack". It is also joked that it could be aliens.

*-Michelle is oblivious to anything going on at the surface and is unsure if she is being held against her will. She hears what she thinks are cars above her room in the bunker.

*- Emmett explains the something is definitely not right on the surface and that the bunker is the safest place to be. Michelle doesn't believe it and tries to escape during dinner (In trailer). 

*-When she looks through the door she witnesses a woman begging to be let into the bunker. Her skin is burning away and she is going insane, she begins banging her head on the door. Next scene jumps to Michelle back in the bunker. 

*-Assuming it's been a few weeks or even months, we see all three characters getting along and hanging out around the bunker. Things are seemingly normal. Howard seems more human with Michelle and often speaks of a girl she assumes was his daughter. She is shown a picture of the girl as well, names Megan.

*-The bunkers Air Filtration System goes down, Michelle is tasked with fixing it since she is the only one who can fit in the Vents (also in trailer). These vents takes her to another bunker room with an escape hatch.

*-After restarting the Air Filtration System, she investigates the room. The hatch has the word "Help" engraved on the window which is also somewhat bloody.  Michelle see's this and also finds a bloody earring from the girl in the picture she had seen.

*-Michelle  goes back into the main bunker and explains this all to Emmett. Emmett tells Michelle that his family left him and Megan was not his daughter, but a friend of Emmett's sister that went to school with him and went missing. 

*-Both Michelle and Emmett conspire an escape by crafting a Hazmat suit/gas mask using Michelle's fashionable skills learned from schooling (The final result seen in the trailer). 

*-Howard gets suspicious and pulls out a circular bin of something which is essentially Acid (seen in the trailer).Howard reveals a pair of scissors they were using and confronts both of them. He demands to know what they are doing with a weapon.

*-Emmett blames himself and says Michelle had nothing to do with it. Howard kills Emmett and disposes of the body by dismantling it and putting it into the Acid (Presumably what he did with Megan).

*-Michelle finishes the suit but Howard catches her before she can put her plan in action. Michelle fights and dumps the acid barrell, Howard falls into it. A fire is also started (seen in trailer). 

*-Michelle steals the suit back and escapes. While on the surface she see's birds. She removes the mask and we learn the air is actually clean. She hears noises and looks around and see's a mysterious ship.

*-It is confirmed that there is actually an attack, and that it is indeed aliens. The bunker blows up, attracting the ship's attention. The ship dispatches some alien dog thing after her that eventually runs away when it finds nothing.

*-She hears noise coming from the house and investigates (Seen in final trailer). Alien ship appears (These ships are Aliens themselves by the way, they have mouths) and Michelle destroys it with a Molotov Cocktail.

*-Michelle leaves the area and picks up a radio signal about the active Alien Invasion. There is talk about the humans winning if they can regroup in Houston. Michelle heads to Houston. The End.

Movie wasn't bad at all. Pretty solid for a brand new director. If you go in not expecting a Cloverfield sequel you will like it. There is a Cloverfield reference however (On a letter from Bold Futura from Cloverfield), if you also do some research you learn the Howard works for the Tagruato Corporation. http://www.slashfilm.com/10-cloverfield-lane-viral/ has lot's of side information about it as well more info about the purpose for the Bunker, the pending attack, and Howard mentioning Megan.

There is also a small reference to Abraham's other monster movie, Super 8 in the form of a Gas Station Michelle stops at before the crash in the beginning of the movie. The gas station was called "Kelvin" which appeared in Super 8. Fun reference. Makes it easy to mesh all the Abrams monster films together in the same universe.

This movie has nothing to do with the monster from the original cloverfield, however this movie takes place near Louisiana and cloverfield took place in New York, at the end of the movie the main girl is listening to a broadcast which says that "human forces have taking back the east coast"

I think there are many monsters involved in this attack, the original cloverfield monster just being one monster. Comment:
I think this movie is related to Cloverfield but that doesn't necessarily mean Clovie is back for a blockbuster sequel. The budget is waaaay to small for a monster movie i feel like. 5 million seems pretty low (even tho Cloverfield had a budget of 25 million which is also very very low so who knows)

But I do think they somehow exist in the same universe for a few reasons. Remember the viral marketing campaign involving Susho and that oil company. Apparently those websites have been inactive for 8 years (since the original came out) but just recently their being updated again. (source: http://cloverfieldclues.blogspot.com/). So something is obviously up with this universe that JJ Abrams has built. I don't know if its necessarily a prequel/sequel/anthology or anything but it's somethin.

Also that bottle she hits him over the head with is a real product called Swamp Pop (you can google it if you want) And on their website there's a product called "Storm shelter supply" for like $4000 that says "out of stock". this could be a way for the company to advertise in a really clever way or another ARG marketing technique. Anyone know anything else? i'm super stoked for this film!

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
Plot: The women wakes up in a underground bunker, shelter and is told by Goodman - that he found her after a horrific accident and brought her here for safety,
Where they remain in shelter - the 3 survivors.  Eventually the Woman starts to trust Goodman less and less and believes that she is not there for her own safety but she is in captivity.
and he might be the monstor. So she tries to flee - Knowing of nothing - No clue as to what remains on the surface
As much as Goodman warns her to stay - She decides to flee.

Very unique.
I read many comments here and I don't believe most of them.
First off it is a sequel that I have heard takes place years after the first film.

My Plot predictions/hints/twists - Based off this trailer:
Why emphasize the buttons he is pressing on the jukebox?  Also it seems like more numbers than usually, - Obviously the writer or director chose these numbers with purpose.
The Poster of the Film:  Shows a house on a barn with a tunnel leading down into the earth's soil which connects to the bunker (this tunnel is also shaped in a "L" - same "L" used in the title for Lane) with a caption that says "Monsters come in many forms".

Using my crazy method of madness I took all this info - watched trailer again and tried to come up with theories.
Why the numbers - 4813?
I searched them up - nothing - I thought I would search them using the words Cloverfield - Nothing
The keywords - New York - hence first film takes place there - Nothing.
I noticed that when the numbers are pushed on the jukebox, it does not show the number one being pressed, only the number 3. This had me thinking that it was part of a sequence

SO, I thought maybe it;s biblical - sense most horrors are biblical in meaning.

search up many biblical texts - keyword 4813 - I found one.
Ephesians 4 8:-13
There is talk of the lord "taking captives, and giving them gifts". i.e., the man and woman John Goodman has "saved". It also speaks about His "ascension" however is does not speak of him going up into the sky and into the heavens. quite the opposite actually. it states: "in saying "He Ascended", what does it mean but that he has also descended INTO the lower regions of the earth."

‚ÄúWhen he ascended on high he led a host of captives,
    and he gave gifts to men.‚Äù[a] 4 8:-13 Epehsians.

Interesting??

This was actually a completely different movie called "The Cellar" that had nothing to do with Cloverfield. it was finished but never released when Paramount's Insurge got canned. It got bought out Paramount proper and they and decided to slap Abraham's name and some re-shot scenes on it and title it like this to flip it and make some money off it.

You are all being had. They are taking a shit, 5 million dollar indie film that had nothing to do with "Cloverfield", giving it this title, and trying to recoup some of their money by baiting and switching. This is gonna be a HUGE fiasco.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment: Based solely on this trailer -- which admittedly doesn't reveal much -- there is something weird about John Gallagher, Jr.'s character. His arm is in a sling throughout the trailer, and you have to wonder what happened to him -- was he in the same car accident as the girl, or did something or someone else cause his injury? He's also almost entirely passive, which might have to do with the whole arm-in-a-sling thing, but think about it -- this woman is being held hostage, handcuffs and all, and he doesn't seem to do anything to help her escape. That in itself is weird, and might suggest that he's in league with John Goodman's character, but the noticeable tension between the two seems to rule that out. Further, when Winstead hits Goodman over the head with a bottle, takes his keys and tries to get out, you don't see Gallagher trying to stop her. It's just odd.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment: I think the trailer actually plays in reverse in terms of its tone. Paramount released their synopsis that mary elizabeth plays a character who wakes up in a bomb shelter after getting into a car accident. It's likely that the shots of her tied to the bed and lifting her phone up are shots of the very beginning of the film of her waking up and trying to receive signal but obviously failing because she is underground. Injured, no communication of the outside world and the sketchy nature of john goodman's character causes her wanting to leave and increases tension within the bunker. Thats where the dinner scene comes in, she hits goodman over the head with the bottle which is important to note. she almost escapes until she sees whatever it is outside or possibly even attacked and goodman might somehow save her and this causes her to change her mind. She goes into the bunker and goodman's character might show them a piece of whats out there, explaining the barrel and him wearing protective gloves for what we can assume is hazardous material. thats when all the happy shots of the trailer kick in because in all of them, john goodman's character has a band aid on his forehead where mary hit him. In terms of what's out there and what's coming, we dont know.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment: Love this trailer because of how much it keeps us in the dark about what could be going on. One of the most interesting things about this trailer, for me at least, is the kind of roar or growl heard while the title is showing near the end. Now I know this isn't a direct sequel to the original Cloverfield, and I haven't watched the original in years, but from what I've heard recently after seeing this trailer, the monster in Cloverfield was only a child. And we know that at the end a nuke was dropped to stop the monster. The growl that is heard when the title shows makes me wonder: Did the monster survive the nuke, or did its mother wake up?

Who knowa, but that is the hallmark of a phenomenal trailer. Take note Zack Snyder, this is how you edit a trailer without spoiling the crap out of your film.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment:
Theory.

John Goodman is a scientist of some type. He knows that the Cloverfield monster is coming. And John Gallagher Jr. is his son. Mary Elizabeth Winstead is his son's girlfriend/wife.
He tries to warn them of the coming apocalypse and the will not heed his warning. So he forced them into his fallout shelter. Hence the broken arm of John Gallagher Jr. and Mary Elizabeth Winstead's need for a crutch in some scenes.
Thinking John Goodman has gone crazy Mary tries to escape. Only to see the world for what it is now. Possibly even seeing the Cloverfield monster or it's spawn.
Hence the scene in the trailer with the biohazard drum. That scene is clearly John Goodman trying to show them the truth. Either before or after Mary's attempted escape.

Title: 10 Cloverfield Lane Official Trailer #1 (2016) -  Mary Elizabeth Winstead, John Goodman Movie HD
Comment: Intriguing. For me Goodman here seems to be some kind of overprotective father, trying to keep those 2 young people from something dangerous they are unaware of and under his total control. The gun in his holster and a short peek of the handcuff on girl's (it seems to me) hand are the details that made me think that. Again what girl sees in the window of the exit door is a total surprise for her - but not for frightened to death Goodman. Plus both youngsters are temporarily crippled (could it be that Goodman intentionally does that to them so they couldn't leave the shelter?) and the old man is the only one fully able there. So I'm almost sure it's a "curiosity killed a [young] cat" story.

Comment:
They've got exactly the kinds of things you'd expect to find in a fallout shelter built in the early '90s -- board games, jigsaw puzzles, books, magazines, what looks like videotapes, a CD jukebox. Things like the lights and fridge may run on outside power, or on a generator. No signs of modern computers other than the cell phone the woman is holding at 0:50.

Based on the synopsis, I get who the woman and the older man are, but who's the guy with his arm in a sling, and what's his relationship to the other characters? Are he and the girl a couple? Is the older man his father?
